.\" termin.al-name: grep
.\" termin.al-usage: grep [-i] [-n] <pattern> [path]
.\" termin.al-summary: Search raw virtual document text.
.TH GREP 1 "" "termin.al" "termin.al Manual"
.ftr B R
.ftr I R
.ftr BI R
.SH NAME
grep \- Search raw virtual document text.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
grep [-i] [-n] <pattern> [path]
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
Searches the raw text of virtual documents. When no path is supplied, the command searches readable documents beneath the current directory within the traversal bound.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B -i
Compare text without ASCII letter case.
.TP
.B -n
Prefix matching lines with their line number.
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
$ grep -n fixture about.md
$ grep -i typed
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
help(1), man(1)
